{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Lost two infants then died at forty","body":"Ann married Dr. Harry Wadsworth in 1807 and bore three children — Harry Jr. in 1806, Theodore in 1807 (lost as an infant the next year), and Betsey Mix in 1809 (lost at age two). Her husband died in 1813, leaving her widowed with one surviving child. She died at forty in 1824."},{"number":2,"category":"marriage","header":"Married her second cousin through Cowles line","body":"Ann's 1807 marriage to Dr. Harry Wadsworth crossed a hundred-year Cowles loop — both descended from Capt. Isaac Cowles of Farmington (1675-1756). Ann came down through Isaac's third-wife son Ezekiel; Harry came down through Isaac's first-wife son Isaac II via Mary Cowles Wadsworth. Half-blood second cousins once removed."}],"slug":"ann-wadsworth-1784"},"H02319":{"id":"H02319","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"title":"Doctor","first_name":"Harry","last_name":"Wadsworth","suffix":"Jr.","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Doctor Harry Wadsworth Jr."},"birth":{"year":1806,"city":"Farmington","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1843,"city":"Austinburg","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"X00267","mother_id":"HD0524"},"marriages":[],"education":[],"career":[{"title":"Physician","type":"medicine","notes":"Physician (M.D.) per EH 1909. Migrated to Austinburg NY where he died at age 36-37."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspi